Sadly, I don't have that much knowledge about that. As far as Research positions, I don't think there are any within our program. You would have to look for opportunities at the eScience Institute or reach out to professors in other departments that are doing research of your interest.  For TA positions within our program, I know they usually look for TAs for¬†DATA 511 (Data Visualization for Data Scientists),¬†DATA 556 (Introduction to Statistics & Probability), and¬†DATA 557 (Applied Statistics & Experimental Design), but they generally ask students that have already taken these classes. If you want to secure a TA position in your first year, I would look for opportunities in other departments, like Engineering. Other departments are always looking for new TAs for undergrad classes that you can apply to.  Also, pay attention to the program's newsletter and look for open positions in Handshake. Sometimes they'll post research positions there, among other jobs at UW. For example, I first learned about my current job as a Data Science Intern at the IT department through the program's newsletter.  I hope that helped! Best, Florencia

Hello Chaitanya  I did my internship in IDRBT through IAS Summer Research Fellowship.  The environment in IDRBT is excellent.   The faculty expects you to complete a project all on your own. This means that you will have to read up books and websites and work on your project by yourself. They will definitely not spoonfeed you, however, you can ask them fpr help if you are stuck in some area.  There is no partiality between IITians and non-IITians. However, they expect you be to be very sharp and be able to take up any kind of challenging project they give. Your peers are going to be extremely knowledgeable and you'll get to learn a lot from them too.  While joining, they do not specifically ask questions on programming knowledge. They do ask how proficient you are in various subjects such as Operating Systems, Computer Netwrking etc.  If you are unable to perform, you can approach your guide/mentor for help, as previously stated, or you can request for a change in the project to something that you are comfortable with.   If you are directly applying to IDRBT through the website, then preference might be given to IITians and NITians over you(GITAM). If you are going through Summer Reasearch fellowship Program as I did, then you have a chance of getting the internship.  I do not know how you have applied or whether you are still planning  to apply but if you get a chance to work at IDRBT you should take it up. It is not going to be easy but you'll definitely love the experience and will learn lots of new things. You will also get an idea about your stand as compared to non-GITAM peers.  All the best.  Regards Anuhya
